Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.69,0:00:03.85,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara-san seemed to be doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.16,0:00:06.62,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,She said her fever had come down.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.62,0:00:09.27,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,She can come to school on Monday.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.61,0:00:12.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't have to go see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.00,0:00:13.65,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,You don't disappoint, detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.83,0:00:17.17,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.50,0:00:19.54,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.98,0:00:21.95,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to thank us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.95,0:00:27.08,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Finding stolen goods is a cinch \Nfor the Silver Detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.08,0:00:28.29,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right, guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.29,0:00:28.88,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.88,0:00:29.57,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.57,0:00:30.30,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.30,0:00:37.30,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Those old guys found a stolen bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.51,0:00:39.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.03,0:00:41.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But the Silver Detectives?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.61,0:00:46.17,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Our group was formed to protect the \Npeace and safety of the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.17,0:00:47.19,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Schwing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.19,0:00:48.36,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Schwing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.36,0:00:49.48,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Schwing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.48,0:00:50.61,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Schwing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.44,0:00:54.49,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,The Silver Detectives!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.53,0:01:00.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, they're a \Ngroup of elderly detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.33,0:01:06.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Propelled forward by the \Nyears spent together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.08,0:01:08.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Charging full speed ahead \Nwithout slowing the pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.05,0:01:11.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A surprising group of rivals appears \Nto challenge the Detective Boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.88,0:01:15.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.42,0:01:17.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.98,0:03:02.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective{\fad(405,1)} Boys VS the Silver Detectives
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.64,0:03:01.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys versus \Nthe Silver Detectives!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.62,0:03:08.37,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,So... you're the famous Detective Boys, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.83,0:03:10.84,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're embarrassing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.84,0:03:14.24,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Akasaka Mutsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.24,0:03:15.25,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Mutsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.92,0:03:22.22,Detective1,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Akasaka Mutsuhiko (70)\NSilver Detective\NRetired Civil Servant
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.00,0:03:18.45,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're Mitsuhiko-kun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.45,0:03:20.21,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Our names are similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.21,0:03:24.14,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}We're both bound by common \Nsense and stubborn, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.44,0:03:26.47,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Stubborn...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.26,0:03:30.10,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Oshima Ginta.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.73,0:03:31.89,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Ginta?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.09,0:03:37.37,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yeah. Like you, I'm a spirited glutton.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:38.44,Detective2,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Oshima Ginta (70)\NSilver Detective\NRetired Shopkeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.44,0:03:40.90,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling a glutton?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.08,0:03:43.25,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm Emoto Yasuko.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.61,0:03:48.29,Detective3,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Emoto Yasuko (70)\NSilver Detective\NApartment Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.25,0:03:46.22,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm just like you, Ayumi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.22,0:03:49.16,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm the token female who \Njust screams all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.35,0:03:50.21,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.76,0:03:53.17,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I do more than scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.42,0:03:59.80,Detective4,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Tokunaga Eitaro (71)\NSilver Detective\NRetired Engineer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.48,0:03:56.04,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm Tokunaga Eitaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.04,0:04:00.67,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Does that make me you, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.26,0:04:03.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to force the comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:09.30,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Silver Detectives, it's time to go on patrol!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.30,0:04:10.98,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.18,0:04:17.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Kiddie Detectives versus \Nthe Silver Detectives, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.50,0:04:25.41,NextDay,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,500)}The Next Day
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.63,0:04:25.43,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.43,0:04:26.95,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.56,0:04:29.45,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.47,0:04:35.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We appreciate you telling \Nus something happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:38.46,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But you guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.46,0:04:43.05,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What? The old folks were the first ones here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.30,0:04:44.17,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.53,0:04:46.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.53,0:04:49.68,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I smell trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.68,0:04:54.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How did you find a body \Ninside a stranger's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.34,0:05:01.38,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I saw a hooligan tossing a \Ncigarette butt in the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.38,0:05:02.36,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, your cigarette!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.98,0:05:07.38,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,When I chided him, \Nhe pushed me and ran off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.38,0:05:10.65,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I called the Silver Detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.65,0:05:13.68,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,And we looked for the hooligan together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.11,0:05:16.42,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.91,0:05:17.93,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.52,0:05:22.77,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He ran into that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:24.31,DCItalic,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.31,0:05:25.59,DCItalic,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,That house, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.59,0:05:26.94,DCItalic,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,He's in that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.94,0:05:27.88,DCItalic,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.21,0:05:31.39,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,We split up and looked for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.82,0:05:34.52,DCItalic,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.43,0:05:41.15,DCItalic,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.37,0:05:42.90,DCItalic,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,C-Call the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.27,0:05:45.36,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,If he's alive, call an ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.36,0:05:47.04,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better check.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.04,0:05:48.41,DCItalic,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.27,0:05:54.22,DCItalic,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.22,0:05:55.74,DCItalic,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Is he alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.14,0:05:56.79,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.78,0:05:58.96,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.65,0:06:01.96,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.32,0:06:07.50,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The victim is Kuroda Kiyomasa,\Ntwenty two, the family's only son.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.30,0:06:10.14,Victim,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Kuroda Kiyomasa (22)\NVictim
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.50,0:06:09.89,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He was struck on the head with an object.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.89,0:06:13.97,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He was killed roughly one hour \Nbefore you discovered his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.23,0:06:19.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why was Inspector Megure scolding you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.22,0:06:23.52,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,This is our first murder scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.05,0:06:26.90,DCItalic,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.47,0:06:34.08,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He must have been hit with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:37.50,DCItalic,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Probably with this edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.92,0:06:43.38,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,They destroyed the crime \Nscene we needed to preserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.68,0:06:44.63,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,We're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.63,0:06:45.32,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.32,0:06:46.22,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.22,0:06:47.38,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.38,0:06:52.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find the hooligan \Nyou were looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:53.00,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.00,0:06:55.67,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,I'd forgotten all about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.67,0:06:56.89,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.32,0:07:02.40,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He must've escaped while we \Nwere distracted by the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.93,0:07:09.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why he ran when all you \Ndid was scold him for littering.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.55,0:07:12.26,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He must've done something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.26,0:07:14.78,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He seemed like a really bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:18.12,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He had gaudy sunglasses, \Na Hawaiian shirt, and bleached hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.75,0:07:21.84,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He had a scar right here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.84,0:07:23.00,DCMain,MITSU,0000,0000,0000,,A scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:25.46,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,As though he'd been cut\Nwith something sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.86,0:07:30.34,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, yeah, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.56,0:07:33.03,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He was tall, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.03,0:07:35.81,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,H-He was pretty tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.81,0:07:39.68,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,He was a tall young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:48.28,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,The victim Kuroda Kiyomasa-san \Nhad a terrible reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.28,0:07:50.57,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,All he ever did was party.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.89,0:07:54.05,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He was probably sponging off someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.05,0:07:58.03,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever was paying him may have killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.03,0:08:01.33,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We'll follow that lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:02.81,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.81,0:08:03.80,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.38,0:08:10.96,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,H-He probably bought this car \Nwith the money he took, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.17,0:08:15.88,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,No, we can't assume that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.88,0:08:18.39,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,We need to redeem ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.44,0:08:23.77,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit would've discarded \Nany incriminating articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.55,0:08:28.19,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Finding them will lead us to the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.19,0:08:29.34,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.89,0:08:36.82,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt they'll find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.82,0:08:40.49,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see if anyone saw anyone suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.49,0:08:41.50,DCMain,MITSHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, let's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.50,0:08:42.29,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.60,0:08:45.79,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're competing with them...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.62,0:08:53.29,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Tossing things into the river is the \Nquickest way to get rid of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.39,0:09:04.06,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,These are the sunglasses \Nthat hooligan was wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.59,0:09:08.79,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this stain...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.57,0:09:12.04,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Is this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.85,0:09:20.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like they didn't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.46,0:09:30.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.68,0:09:32.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.77,0:09:38.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The Silver Detectives found \Nsome bloodstained sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.25,0:09:42.51,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It was the victim's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.68,0:09:43.89,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.08,0:09:51.14,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the murderer was \Nthe hooligan we were chasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.90,0:09:57.74,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He snuck into that house, \Nkilled the victim, and fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.19,0:10:02.66,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Realizing he'd left evidence \Nat the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.33,0:10:08.27,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,he hurried back, destroyed \Nthe evidence, and ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.44,0:10:16.85,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Noticing the victim's \Nblood on his sunglasses,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.41,0:10:20.64,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,he threw them in the river \Nto destroy the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.04,0:10:23.51,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.51,0:10:24.68,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.89,0:10:28.64,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What did the hooligan look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.98,0:10:31.02,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He was blond and wearing a Hawaiian shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.25,0:10:33.27,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,He had a scar right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.87,0:10:35.78,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,He was really tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.01,0:10:38.28,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,He was a young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.81,0:10:40.70,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Start looking for him immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.65,0:10:47.23,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,They made an incredible discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.23,0:10:50.22,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,They beat us to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.22,0:10:52.02,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.89,0:10:54.88,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.88,0:10:58.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it seems too perfect?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.08,0:10:58.76,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.95,0:11:03.25,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose it does sound rather perfect...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.25,0:11:07.02,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Those old dudes got really lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.53,0:11:12.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did they form a\Ndetective group, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.42,0:11:19.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Something's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.32,0:11:29.41,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? The stolen bicycle?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.66,0:11:32.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. How did you find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.93,0:11:41.43,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, someone told Tokunaga-san \Nabout a stolen red bicycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.43,0:11:43.64,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then we all went looking for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.08,0:11:49.35,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Tokunaga-san deduced where a \Nthief would abandon a bicycle,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.35,0:11:50.64,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,and that's where we found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.87,0:11:54.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Tokunaga-san did?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.05,0:12:01.38,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, I only told the police \Nmy bicycle was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.38,0:12:03.99,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,But they knew it was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.39,0:12:06.82,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detectives are amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.82,0:12:08.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.71,0:12:13.52,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's split up and investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.52,0:12:14.00,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.93,0:12:22.67,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.31,0:12:25.24,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll start.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.24,0:12:29.68,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The Silver Detectives formed one month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.89,0:12:33.43,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Tokunaga-san put out an ad \Nin the city's PR magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.43,0:12:34.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.44,0:12:37.19,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for members!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.70,0:12:37.19,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.47,0:12:42.69,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Now, why did he form a detective group?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.23,0:12:44.99,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.11,0:12:46.11,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.36,0:12:51.76,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Someone in the apartment \Nnext door had just died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.76,0:12:57.42,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,An old lady named Kano Tae fell down the \Nstairs at the station and hit her head.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.70,0:13:02.64,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,She'd just withdrawn three \Nmillion yen from the bank,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.64,0:13:05.93,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,so someone attacked her for the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.16,0:13:11.68,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Tokunaga-san formed a detective \Ngroup to find the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.99,0:13:15.06,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, that's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.40,0:13:16.89,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.89,0:13:21.11,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Kano-san died in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.60,0:13:26.53,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,She tripped on the stairs because \None of her legs was broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.75,0:13:29.78,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,So no one pushed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.88,0:13:32.16,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.16,0:13:36.96,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,She broke her leg when a car hit her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.28,0:13:45.34,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Tokunaga-san formed a detective \Ngroup to find the person who ran her over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.67,0:13:47.97,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.19,0:13:49.22,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.55,0:13:53.63,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,We know who hit her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.63,0:13:58.39,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's the recently deceased \NKuroda Kiyomasa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.51,0:13:59.64,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.64,0:14:00.31,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.57,0:14:07.20,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But he seemed sincerely apologetic,\Nso she didn't report him to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.58,0:14:14.36,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Several days later, she died after \Nwithdrawing three million yen from the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.21,0:14:19.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That money...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.35,0:14:22.38,DCItalic,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He was probably sponging off someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.90,0:14:26.85,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He seemed sincere despite his reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.64,0:14:31.99,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could he have planned it all along?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.99,0:14:33.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.41,0:14:36.71,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.13,0:14:38.99,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you figure something out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.99,0:14:40.39,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.39,0:14:47.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Only Tokunaga-san had any useful \Ninformation about the hooligan, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.65,0:14:48.44,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.91,0:14:51.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't because they're old.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.59,0:14:54.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's like "The Emperor's Snuff-box."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.29,0:14:56.84,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.84,0:14:59.25,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What's a snuff-box?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.48,0:15:04.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a mystery novel written \Nby John Dickson Carr,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.91,0:15:09.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the king of locked-room mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.63,0:15:18.11,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,We still can't find that hooligan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.11,0:15:19.78,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.78,0:15:21.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're wasting your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.93,0:15:27.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.28,0:15:28.67,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.18,0:15:31.15,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Why not, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.53,0:15:35.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did the hooligan really have \Nbleached hair and a Hawaiian shirt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.22,0:15:38.04,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.31,0:15:41.46,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Did he really have a scar here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:43.06,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Was he tall?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.41,0:15:45.34,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Was he a young man?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.74,0:15:47.71,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.91,0:15:51.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of Hawaiian shirt was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.01,0:15:54.99,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,One with lots of palm trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.99,0:15:56.38,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,It was yellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.99,0:15:56.38,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,It was red.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.99,0:15:56.38,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.38,0:15:57.60,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.60,0:16:00.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Your answers don't match.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.96,0:16:02.89,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.16,0:16:06.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a famous mystery novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.33,0:16:11.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even though a character hasn't seen anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.97,0:16:14.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,they start to believe another \N person who insists they have.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.07,0:16:19.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.02,0:16:22.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he never existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.69,0:16:24.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Tokunaga-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.99,0:16:29.88,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.09,0:16:35.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You knew the victim, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.42,0:16:39.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Because he hit Kano Tae-san with his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.47,0:16:43.02,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Who's Kano Tae-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.02,0:16:45.43,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Er, Tokunaga-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.43,0:16:48.26,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,You knew the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.85,0:16:56.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't forgive Kuroda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.72,0:17:02.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He deliberately hit Kano \NTae-san with his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.68,0:17:07.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He won over Kano-san with his sincerity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.64,0:17:11.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He tricked her into giving him money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.64,0:17:21.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kano-san died because she \Nwent to withdraw money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.76,0:17:26.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kuroda-san's evil scheme \Nbasically killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.56,0:17:31.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to get revenge on \NKuroda-san with your own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.85,0:17:33.28,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.92,0:17:35.64,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,You're out of your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.01,0:17:37.66,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I would never...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:43.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't want any witnesses, \Nso you killed him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.78,0:17:46.19,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I would get caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.19,0:17:49.67,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,People leave their hair everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.12,0:17:53.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you "discovered" \Nthe body first.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.05,0:17:56.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you left anything at the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.56,0:17:59.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,you could pretend it happened then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.89,0:18:06.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But the police always suspect \Nwhoever discovers a crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:07.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so you couldn't do it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.62,0:18:13.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You had to get inside to discover \Nthe body, so you needed an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.77,0:18:17.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you formed this detective group.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.73,0:18:22.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You waited for an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.84,0:18:29.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You visited Kuroda-san while \Nhis family was away on vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.08,0:18:32.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.71,0:18:35.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You left the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.81,0:18:42.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,threw the bloodstained sunglasses in the \Nriver, and gathered your detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.58,0:18:46.27,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,He ran into that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.27,0:18:47.99,DCItalic,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.99,0:18:49.20,DCItalic,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,That house, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.20,0:18:50.31,DCItalic,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,He's in that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.31,0:18:51.27,DCItalic,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.63,0:18:55.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You entered the Kuroda family home
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.92,0:18:58.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to look for an imaginary hooligan \Nand discovered the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.80,0:19:01.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Like amateur detectives,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.28,0:19:06.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,you "accidentally" erased the\Nmurderer's fingerprints
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.05,0:19:09.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,that never existed in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.82,0:19:13.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning, you formed the Silver Detectives
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.15,0:19:22.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so you could discover the body \Ntogether and avoid suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.57,0:19:24.84,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Tokunaga-san, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.84,0:19:25.72,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you really...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.25,0:19:27.89,DCMain,TASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.72,0:19:30.77,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Conan-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.03,0:19:36.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You had to discover the sunglasses to cast \Nsuspicion on your imaginary hooligan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.89,0:19:41.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But such a sudden and incredible \Ndiscovery would be too good to be true,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.08,0:19:43.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so you fabricated a precedent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.28,0:19:47.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You stole a bicycle and pretended to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.59,0:19:52.62,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen the victim before today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.93,0:19:57.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But you knew which car \Nbelonged to Kuroda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.90,0:20:03.38,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,H-He probably bought this car \Nwith the money he took, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.50,0:20:07.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you waited for an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.02,0:20:13.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The police would eventually \Nnotice the connection
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.95,0:20:17.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,between the victim and a man \Nwho discovered the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.93,0:20:21.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They wouldn't consider it a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.52,0:20:26.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Once they investigated you, \Nthey would find conclusive evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.85,0:20:29.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,By then, it'll be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.16,0:20:31.45,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But you still have time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.45,0:20:36.42,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,You can turn yourself in \Nbefore they suspect you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.42,0:20:38.29,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It will lessen your sentence!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.49,0:20:41.80,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You children...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.56,0:20:46.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We just want you to admit you were \Nwrong and atone for your crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.62,0:20:49.35,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Tokunaga-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.90,0:20:56.35,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,When Kano-san died, I visited Kuroda.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.92,0:21:00.36,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I thought if only her leg \Nhadn't been broken...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.00,0:21:04.63,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,You should come pay your respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.57,0:21:06.91,DCItalic,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,That useless hag.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.12,0:21:10.20,DCItalic,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,She should've given me her \Nmoney before she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.21,0:21:13.00,DCItalic,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The three million...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.46,0:21:17.33,DCItalic,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,I just need to hit my \Nnext target with my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.29,0:21:23.20,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I learned he had planned it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.70,0:21:26.46,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I pitied Kano-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.16,0:21:31.72,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I used you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.23,0:21:35.33,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. More importantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.33,0:21:37.50,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.50,0:21:39.67,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.67,0:21:41.65,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Before it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.47,0:21:45.65,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Children...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.83,0:21:48.03,DCMain,TOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.34,0:23:18.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.80,0:23:21.92,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,They want to be our apprentices.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.92,0:23:22.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.79,0:23:25.05,DCMain,MUTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Please make us your apprentices!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.05,0:23:27.20,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll buy you eel bowls!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.20,0:23:29.59,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I promise not to scream!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.24,0:23:35.46,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.70,0:23:42.64,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If they can run like that, \Nthey shouldn't need senior bus passes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.00,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.38,0:23:46.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.33,0:23:48.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.56,0:23:52.24,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What are they looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.40,0:23:54.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Probably a spring mirage.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.16,0:23:57.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uozu is famous for its mirages.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.99,0:24:00.52,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.00,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Mirage of the Disappearing Angel
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.48,0:24:13.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"Mirage of the Disappearing Angel!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.03,0:24:35.03,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Digital Camera
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.48,0:24:32.80,DCMain,Genta,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.80,0:24:35.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A digital camera!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.03,0:24:40.03,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.36,0:24:36.61,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Don't be bound by common sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.61,0:24:37.73,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Eat light!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.73,0:24:38.76,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Don't scream!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.76,0:24:39.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Well, that's impossible.
